<p>Is Milan a safe city? This doubt could arise in someone&#39;s mind fascinated by the idea of visiting the Italian capital of fashion. The options to get informed, nowadays are many: from the most common “word of mouth” to the several platforms on the web where users from all over the world can share their personal experiences and opinions. From our milanese headquarter, the Solede&#39;s team can happily assure that in principle, like any major city in Europe, Milan offers a safe urban environment. </p>

<h3>Milan in The Safe Cities Index 2015</h3>

<p>According to the recent list of the most secure cities in the world drawn up by the Economist (<a href="http://safecities.economist.com/whitepapers/safe-cities-index-white-paper/">The Safe Cities Index 2015</a>), Milan holds the 26th position. The report is based on an index composed of more than 40 quantitative and qualitative indicators divided in four thematic categories: health security; digital security; infrastructure safety and personal safety. Thanks to this investigation, Milan confirms its regular position in the global panorama (even if significantly behind other large European cities) and gains the first place within the national context. </p>

